ce:section.ce:para:
The structure of the functionalized CQDs was shown in Scheme 1
                        . It consists of three fragment: Mal-PEG-NHS, RGERPPR and CQD. The experimental process were listed as follows:

                              1.

Take 10 ml of CQDs solution, and then weighed 50 mg maleimide-polyethylene glycol-aminosuccinyl imine succinate, and the mixture was mixed in a 50 ml flask;


                              2.

5 drops of triethylamine was added to the flask as a catalyst, adjust the pH of the solution to 7–9 and the reaction was carried out overnight at room temperature;


                              3.

The reaction was dialyzed against a dialysis bag with a molecular weight of 500 for 3 days;


                              4.

The resulting material was lyophilized and mixed with 100 mg of tumor-penetrating peptide (RGERPPR) in a flask, the solvent was N, N-dimethylformamide (DMF);


                              5.

Adjust the pH of the solution to 5–7.5 and the reaction was carried out overnight at room temperature;


                              6.

The reaction was dialyzed against a dialysis bag with a molecular weight of 500 for 3 days, and then lyophilized;


                              7.

The resulting product was partitioned into an aqueous solution for further characterization.

After 16 days of intracranial transplantation by U87 cell line, the gliomas grew up to 2.2 mm width and 2.4 mm height (Fig. 5
                         A). After the death of the nude mice, the tumor size was measured with a vernier caliper, the diameter of 2.29 mm (Fig. 6
                        ) was consistent with NMR experimental results.
